<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Mineral Products Association (CYS0048)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Written evidence from Mineral Products Association (CYS0048)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The Minerals Products Association (MPA) is the trade association representing the aggregates, asphalt</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> cement, concrete and related industries. Our industry delivers 200 million tonnes of materials to customers in the UK every year. While the industry is a major user of road and sea/water transport modes, most materials are delivered to customers by road a</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">nd the industry is a major user of the road network. As most construction activity is in urban areas our industry is also a significant user of urban roads.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">This follow up inquiry follows recent cyclist fatalities in London and we would like to make concis</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">e comments on two areas highlighted n the Committee’s request for evidence.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">What central and local Government could do to improve cycling </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">safety.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> Ideas could include better training and advice for drivers and cyclists, better enforcement of the law applyin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">g to drivers and cyclists, and better vehicle and road infrastructure.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Driver training, vehicle equipment and procurement conditions</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">MPA introduced a Cycle Safety Strategy in 2011 with six broad aims, as follows:</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Promote Driver and Industry Awareness</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Promote Cyclist and Public Awareness</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Improve Driver Training</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Encourage Members  to use Appropriate Technological Adaptations to Minimise Risks to Cyclists and Exchange Experience</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Liaise with Schools</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Work in Partnership</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">In 2012 we followed this up with a Vu</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">lnerable Road User</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> Safety</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> Policy covering the delivery of materials on behalf of member companies in the main types of industry delivery vehicles, tippers, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">truckmixers</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and tankers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The policy includes</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> requirements for specific vulnerable road user training</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> for drivers, the fitting of blind spot </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">elimination equipment to large goods </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">vehicles</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> such as nearside cameras and/or side sensors) and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">sideguard</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> protection to all tipper lorries (this is not a leg</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">al requirement currently). The</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> policy applies to </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">ne</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">w </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">vehic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">les and there is also a retrofitting requirement for existing vehicles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> In addition action by MPA and member companies includes:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The industry’s training or</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">ganisation (the MPQC) has implemented</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> an officially approved training course for drivers on safeguarding vulnerable road users – to date 1,000 drivers have successfully completed the course</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">MPA members have participated in over 50 Exchanging Places events with the Met Police to help give cycl</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">ists an awareness of the HGV driver’s environment and visibility.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> Similar events have also been run in other parts of the UK.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Member companies are also engaged in school visits to highlight road safety awareness for children and teachers. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">MPA is</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> now wor</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">king closely with Transport for London </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">and other interested parties </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">on the development of procurement guidelines for construction clients and contractors to use – covering vulnerable road user safety issues through the delivery supply chain.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> The intention is that these guidelines will be regarded as a consistent national standard for application to construction contracts.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">From the perspective of the major supply sector for the construction industry we believe that the approach which we have </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">adopted, focussing on high quality driver training and the fitting of appropriate equipment to </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Large Goods Vehicles, should make a positive contribution to cycling safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Enforcement</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> - General</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Enforcement of regulations by all road users is a key aspect</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> of improving </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">road safety. We have no difficulty in active enforcement of LGVs as it is unreasonable if poor operators with low operating standards are allowed to undermine operators with higher standards.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Enforcement – Specific Issue</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">In addition we have</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> b</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">een urging Government since 2010</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> to take action to close regulatory loopholes which allow certain types of engineering plant to operate on public roads with very little regul</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">atory control. Specifically, so-</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">called Volumetric Plant are currently permitted </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">to deliver large volumes of concrete to customers </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">( we</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> estimate 2 million cubic metres of ready mixed concrete per annum – 10% of the total market). </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">The legal position is that there is a definition of Engineering Plant covering plant/vehicles which are spe</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">cifically designed for use in engineering operations - e.g. road construction plant - but this</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">definition is not designed to include road going vehicles. Engineering plant </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">have</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">much lighter regulatory requirements than LGVs, for example:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">Drivers of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">engineering plant d</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">o not have to adhere to</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal"> Drivers Hours rules or use </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">tachographs</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">Drivers of engineering plant are in general only required to have category B driving</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">licences (the standard driving licence for cars and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">vehicles up to 3.5 tonnes</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">), not LGV</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal"> licences.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">There is no requirement for operators of engineering plant to have Operators (O) licences - so the Transport Commissioners cannot take sanctions against an operator for persistent roadworthiness infringements, as they can for LGV operators.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">Engineering plant are in general exempt from LGV testing and plating requirements</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">LGV weight restrictions do not appear to apply to volumetric plant. Whereas a 4 axle rigid HGV will be limited to 32 tonnes gross vehicle weight, it appears common practi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">ce for a similar size volumetric plant to operate at over 40 tonnes.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">In general engineering plant should be limited to 30mph on motorways and 12 mph on other roads, but there is no evidence that these limits are enforced for volumetric plant.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">We believe</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> that all vehicles/plant delivering construction materials</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> should be subject to common LGV regulations and that if Government does not take urgent action to ensu</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">re that volumetric plant are</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> regulated to LGV standards there are clear and adverse implication</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">s for road safety and in particular for the safety of vulnerable road users. We have been pressing Government to take such action since 2010 and are extremely disappointed that no material action has been taken in spite of the outstanding and obvious case </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">to do so.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Whether it would be desirable and feasible to segregate cyclists from other road users, including, for example, by prohibiting HGVs from entering city centres at peak hours.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">We support the segregation of cyclists from other road users where this is possible but this is not likely to be feasible in all cases given the limited road space available in many urban areas. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">There has been some discussion of rush hour lorry bans but </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">there are real practical issues that need recognition and consideration, for example:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">There is unlikely to be</span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">any simple cause and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> effect for the recent cycling fatalities</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">. Subject to the findings of more detailed investigations there appears to have been </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">a variety of issues involved in recent incidents.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Curren</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">tly the timing of construction L</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">GV deliveries is constrained by access to both construction sites and at materials supply sources (depots, concrete, asphalt plants etc) by the hours of working and tra</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">ffic restrictions</span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">allowed in planning permissions. Therefore in many cases there is limited capacity to deliver before and after the main rush hours. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">We believe that the possibility of altering current planning conditions to allow for longer working hours</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> at construction sites and material supply </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">sources is remote and in any case a longer term issue. We already have difficulties in operating sites on current conditions due to the encroachment of residential development into previously non residential areas</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> and population growth suggests that this will be an issue of increasing rather than reducing conflict. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Consequently rush hour bans would concentrate deliveries in a sm</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">aller daytime delivery window. For example t</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">his would mean a much higher concentration</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> of deli</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">veries within the 10.00 am to 04</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">.00 pm period </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">if </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">07.00 to 10.00</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">am</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> and 04.00 to 07</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">.00</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> pm rush hour bans were introduced.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Even if it was possible to mobilise more</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">delivery </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">vehicles in a smaller window (</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">a questionable issue as the availability of both</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> vehicles and drivers is alread</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">y constrained) it may</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> not be possible to deliver enough materials to sustain current rates of progress of construction contracts. As an example there is the need for many larger </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">construction </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">contracts to have continuous pours</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> of concrete requiring significant deliveries over an extended period.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Is there any evidence that more concentrated delivery windows resulting from rush hour bans would improve </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">overall road safety</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">There is a broader issue about the impact on economic </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">activity in London</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> and other cities arising from more restricted delivery hours</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">. From a transport perspective a business model involving more concentrated delivery hours, therefore more vehicles and drivers for this period and little work outside the windo</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">w, looks a very difficult model on which to make a reason</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">able financial return</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">. Similarly, significant restrictions on delivery times would reduce the operating hours of our sites and plant, which again is a very difficult and inefficient business model. U</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">ltimately supply chain costs would increase to accommodate such operational inefficiencies, feeding through into higher construction and development costs.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">MPA Resources and Related Information </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">MPA</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Policy Document</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">MPA has produced a two-sided document outlining our Vulnerable 